               <p>RALPH ROSSI. I am a <rs id="t18280110-222-viclabel1168" type="occupation">wine-merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-222-victim1315 t18280110-222-viclabel1168"></join>. I was packing in my warehouse about seven o'clock on the 2d of January - my boy went to the door, and called Stop thief! I went out, missed the truck, and found the prisoner with it almost directly.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-222-person1316">
                  THOMAS 
                  EVERITT
               <interp inst="t18280110-222-person1316" type="surname" value="EVERITT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-222-person1316" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-222-person1316" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in Mr. Rossi's employ. I opened the warehouse door, hearing a noise, and saw the prisoner going along with the truck - he left it, and ran; I pursued, and never lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He came up and asked if I was not the man- I waited at a public-house for five minutes; the boy said he beleived it was me; the officer said it would not do to believe - then he said he was sure.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-222-person1317">
                  THOMAS 
                  EVERITT
               <interp inst="t18280110-222-person1317" type="surname" value="EVERITT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-222-person1317" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-222-person1317" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The first thing I said to him was,"What are you doing with that truck?" he said he did<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182801100105"></xptr>not touch it; I left him at the public-house door, and went back to master.</p>
               <p>RALPH ROSSI. I did not wish to prosecute him, and left him at the public-house, but some persons gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
